==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Losel
<hw>Los"el</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the root of
<ets>lose</ets>, <ets>loss</ets>. ⟦root⟧127. Cf. <er>Lorel</er>.]</ety>
<def>One who loses by sloth or neglect; a worthless person; a
lorel.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One sad <qex>losel</qex> soils a name for aye.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Losel</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Losel
<hw>Los"el</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Wasteful; slothful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Losenger</ent>⟦br⟧
